"PBS NewsHour."

00:49.316 --> 00:52.085 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:52.119 --> 01:01.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Another big seat
is filled
in the Trump Cabinet-to-be, and
it sets up

01:01.662 --> 01:04.064 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a potential confirmation fight.

01:04.097 --> 01:08.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect's transition
team confirmed
this morning that a top oil
executive is the

01:08.936 --> 01:12.205 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
choice for secretary of state.

01:12.239 --> 01:17.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After days of speculation,
official word of
the Rex Tillerson pick came
before sunrise,

01:17.911 --> 01:20.881 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
followed by praise from the vice
president-elect.

01:20.914 --> 01:25.152 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE PENCE (R), Vice
President-Elect: We just
could not be more grateful that
someone of

01:25.185 --> 01:30.190 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Rex Tillerson's proven
leadership and accomplishments
has been willing to step forward
to serve

01:30.223 --> 01:33.226 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
our nation as our next secretary
of state.

01:33.260 --> 01:39.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Tillerson, a
native Texan,
is currently CEO of oil giant
ExxonMobil,

01:39.066 --> 01:42.302 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
among the world's largest
publicly traded
companies.

01:42.336 --> 01:48.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He rose through the ranks over
four decades,
and, as chief executive, he's
expanded ExxonMobil's

01:48.675 --> 01:52.946 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
business overseas, including its
operations
in Russia.

01:52.980 --> 01:59.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a 2013 interview with Charlie
rose for
CBS News, Tillerson made clear
his company

01:59.586 --> 02:01.088 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will go wherever there's oil.

02:01.121 --> 02:04.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REX TILLERSON, Chairman &amp; CEO,
ExxonMobil:
My philosophy is to make money.

02:04.091 --> 02:09.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so if I can drill and make
money, then
that's what I want to do.

02:09.963 --> 02:15.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it really is -- for us, it's
about making
quality investments for our
shareholders.

02:15.602 --> 02:20.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: To that end,
ExxonMobil began
working closely with the Russian
state-owned

02:20.207 --> 02:21.975 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
oil giant Rosneft.

02:22.009 --> 02:29.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That, in turn, brought Tillerson
into close
contact with Russian President
Vladimir Putin.

02:29.049 --> 02:34.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since then, he's received the
Russian Order
of Friendship, and he's said he
opposes U.S.

02:34.988 --> 02:40.694 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and European sanctions against
Russia over
its intervention in Ukraine.

02:40.727 --> 02:45.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senate Majority Leader Mitch
McConnell today
highlighted Tillerson's
experience, and said

02:45.665 --> 02:48.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he looks forward to supporting
his nomination.

02:48.902 --> 02:54.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the top Democrat on the
Senate Foreign
Relations Committee, Ben Cardin,
said he is

02:54.074 --> 03:00.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
