provides more than
$6 billion.

05:27.961 --> 05:31.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It also streamlines the process
for approving
drugs and medical devices.

05:31.598 --> 05:35.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Obama spoke before signing
the bill at
a White House ceremony with
lawmakers and

05:35.835 --> 05:37.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Vice President Biden.

05:37.671 --> 05:41.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
We are bringing to reality the
possibility

05:41.942 --> 05:46.046 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of new breakthroughs to some of
the greatest
health challenges of our time.

05:46.079 --> 05:50.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm confident that it will lead
to better
years and better lives for
millions of Americans,

05:50.283 --> 05:51.484 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the work that you have done.

05:51.518 --> 05:54.020 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's what we got sent here
for.

05:54.054 --> 05:56.756 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The new law
also includes
funding for mental health.

05:56.790 --> 05:58.792 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will explore that later in
the program.

05:58.825 --> 06:03.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In Russia,
opposition political
leader Alexei Navalny announced
that he will

06:03.830 --> 06:06.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
run for president in 2018.

06:06.466 --> 06:11.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
